init_text: When you're 28, science discovers a drug that stops all effects of aging, creating immortality. Your government decides to give the drug to all citizens under 26, but you and the rest of the "Lost Generations" are deemed too high-risk. When you're 85, the side effects are finally discovered.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You're given the choice: take the drug or die.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: His wife, however, was not ready to let him go.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: She decided to take matters into her own hands.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He was sitting at the table, and she was cooking.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He took a sip of his tea, and then another.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: She thought about it for a moment.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "I know, but I'll be right back." she said.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: She left the room, and went to the kitchen.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The man was still sitting there, thinking about his last day on earth.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He thought of every bad thing he'd ever done.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He got up from the table, and walked out the front door.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: looked up at the sky, and saw the stars.
